  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Humanitarian Response and Support for Violent Attacks-affected Population in Zango-Kataf</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The activities will be carried out by SF member through identified partners. The trainings and awareness on EWS and emergency response will be led by the Local partner 1, Kaduna Branch and the protection theme led by Local partner 2, rapid assessments, PDM, monitoring and evaluation will be led by SF member and procurement of NFIs led by local partner 2 and distribution supported by Local partner 1 through its pool of volunteers. All stakeholders&apos; engagements will be jointly carried out by SF member and local partners and cash distribution conducted through cash vendors to be engaged by SF member</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project targets 3,000 households (21,000 individuals) in need. This is based on an average household size of 7 individuals, as recommended by the UN food security cluster. The activities include:

1. 3,000 households will benefit from Shelter/NFI and WASH distribution
2. 1,500 HH for cash distribution as would be further determined by wealth-ranking, vulnerability assessment and market survey as more detailed vulnerability analysis will be undertaken to determine these beneficiaries
3. Community sensitisation on topics such as GBV and on disaster preparedness</narrative>
  </description>
